commit_message:
Merge pull request #10 from nik875/master

Fixed deprecated BioPython Seq Alphabet
enqueue_write_buffer does not exists anymore in pyOpenCL
DNA/RNA scoring now allows for ambiguous nucleotides
Scripts needed to demultiplex pacbio data

Merge branch 'cl_optimizations' of
https://github.com/StreamHPC/pyPaSWAS.git into streamcomputing

Conflicts:
	.gitignore
Remove unused kernel arg, change order of work groups

Make directions matrix not zero-copy for GPU

It improves performance on AMD slightly (because this data is written and read more often by kernels than by host).
Maximize number of targets when number of sequences is small

Fix calculation of number of targets/sequences

Correctly calculate memory used by matrices (especially when gap_extension is enabled).
Correctly limit number of targets using the current target's length (not the first one, i.e. longest)
Improve sorting of hits by Formatter
Remove SmithWatermanNVIDIA as it has same (or lower) performance
Optimize traceback by checking in calculateScore if it is required
Implement detailed output of current progress and performance
Add line number and file name befor source code for better error messages
Skip reading starting points and direction buffers when no points found
Reallocate buffers only when they are too small

Use the same program for all launches

Preprocessor definitions are replaced by kernel parameters. Program and kernel objects are cached.

Merge pull request #3 from mkempenaar/master

Docker images containing pyPaSWAS
Fixed links to docker container files
Added Docker instructions and container description files

Improve performance on AMD GPUs

Do not call kernels using program.kernel_name, because this way creates
a new kernel and queries the kernel's info every call, which is slow on
AMD platform.
Corrected memory check for gap extension
Added timing data, scripts and R Markdown reports
added the -g option for gap extension penalty
Fixed typo and removed unneeded calcs
First affine gap implementation finished. Needs testing
GPU openCL code for affine gap
Cuda implementation of affine gap finished
Affinge gap in CUDA scoring implemented
Making start with the affine gap penalty
removed code for combar and moved that to own repository
BUg in OCL code: duplicate fill_character
Bug fix in openCL: fill character was wrong
pyPaSWAS now support up-to 255 characters for scoring (char range -1).
Nodes name for Neo4J are now customizable
Neo4j graph database connection and storing alignments as graphs

Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/palindrome' into palindrome

Conflicts:
	pyPaSWAS/pypaswasall.py
Added options to process parts of the input files.
Added options for palindrome to config
Palindrome now works read vs. read
Added the ability to limit processing of seeds with fraction_of_seeds
Major update on the GenomePlotter. Now works in CUDA and OpenCL
Changed memory buffer flags in ComBaR OpenCL code
Added the option to select OpenCL sub devices
Window length was not in index
Fixed bug with config file and added new version number to SAM
Fixed small bug in CUDA/OpenCL for ComBaR

Moved debug statement and lowered number of windows processed in single
step
Increased the internal step size for building the index
Location in reference sequence for mapping was incorrect
CUDA indexer now steps through long sequences
Fixed stepping to far in genome with windows
Check for number of locations: none found, skip all reads
Changed bit order calculations and added fraction
start window could be zero. Fixed
Creation of index now in CUDA.
Changed version number in sam header
Added option reads_to_process to command line
Odd characters in sequence will not create error
working on processing more than read with mapping
Merge branch 'qindexerParallel' of https://github.com/swarris/pyPaSWAS.git into qindexerParallel
Indexer failed on references shorter than window length
Popping context in CUDA while running SW should be done at end process
Size of index was too large for gpu
Added openCL implementation of finding indices
Created CUDA implementation for finding indices

Set count to overlap method and sped up indexer by counting only
relevant locations
Added the indexer program and set compressed index as default

Added the option to compress the index files. Compressing large files in
python with zlib creates memory leaks!
Changed selection order and made GPU Opencl default
Changed some debug to info and added blosum80 matrix
Speed up of copying min_score to device
removed loops from align_sequences (were moved to methods)
switch to scipy to test memory usage
Merge branch 'qindexer' of https://github.com/swarris/pyPaSWAS.git into qindexer
Switched calc_distance from scipy linear algebra to numpy.linalg.
Switched to scipy for sparse matrices.
Fixed indexer: prevCount was not set
Updated config, now default: Intel CPU Opencl
Removed old indexer and set compression to 1 for QIndexer

Merge branch 'pyopencl' of https://github.com/swarris/pyPaSWAS.git into
pyopencl

Conflicts:
	pyPaSWAS/Core/SmithWatermanOcl.py
Probably fixed globalDirection reads in CPU version of OpenCL, needs proper testing though
Removed a bug in the initialization of d_matrix in case of a CPU

Problems with allocating memory for devices. 
Also globalMaxima matrix is overallocated: need to fix this (only end
result maximum needs to be stored, not all maxima).
Changed openCL device selection based on config
Merge branch 'pyopencl' of https://github.com/swarris/pyPaSWAS into pyopencl
Proper way of getting device memory information
Added a define in the compilation step of the NVIDIA kernel
added class SmithWatermanNVIDIA for nvidia opencl gpu runs
add set and get direction methods
Further subdivided the inheritance relationship of between cpu and gpu implementations of opencl
made distinction in how datastructures are initialized for CPU and GPU
Made a seperate kernel codebase for GPU and CPU
added the functionality to choose between different parallel programming frameworks
Changed the way in which the zero-copy buffers were read from the host
made device and platform selection more robust
Created subclasses for Cuda(SmithWatermanCuda.py) and OpenCL(SmithWatermanOcl.py). Subclasses have to be filled in.
Fixed bug, not all alignments were kept
Too many short reads in memory were allowed
Changed QIndexer from nonoverlapping to overlapping index
Depricated most part of Indexer, with qgram=1 now also QIndexer is used
Added memory configuration to config file
Set correct version number in SAM header
Bug fix in the read mapping algorithm: print_alignment got wrong index
Fixed exception handling at main level in pypaswas.py
Made the ComBar Indexer / Mapper more stable against index file removal
Changed the way pypaswas is called
Added a basic wrapper, making the -m option unnecessary
First commit, copy from Google Code
